**SANSKRIT TEXT GUIDANCE:**
- This text is classical Sanskrit (Krishi-Parashara, Vriksha Ayurveda, or similar).
- Verses (shlokas) end with ।or ॥. Each shloka is a complete unit of knowledge.
- If commentary (bhashya) follows a verse, extract meaning from the commentary, not the raw Sanskrit.
- Preserve technical Sanskrit agricultural terms AS-IS in subject/object (e.g., balīvarda, gomaya, jalī, kṣetra).
- Use type="observation" for weather/astronomical/seasonal rules (nakshatra-based timing, cloud formations, animal behaviour predictors).
- Use type="practice" for specific farming operations described in the verses.
- Set confidence 0.55–0.70 for archaic/ambiguous terms; do NOT hallucinate translations.
- Evidence snippets may be in Sanskrit script — copy verbatim, do not transliterate.

